@page
@using H24.Models;
@model H24.Pages.LaserCut.DescentModelsModel

@{
    ViewData["Title"] = @Model.Title;
}

<div class="card">
    <partial name="../Common/CardHeader.cshtml" for="@Model" />
    <div class="card-body">
        <partial name="../Common/ParagraphStart.cshtml" />
        Using <a href="http://www.123dapp.com/make">Autodesk 123D Make</a>, I converted the
        <a href="http://www.descent2.com/goodies/3dmodels/thinman/descent1/">Class 1 & Class 2</a> drones from the
        <a href="http://www.interplay.com/games/descent.php">Descent</a> video game to physical models.
        <partial name="../Common/ParagraphEnd.cshtml" />
        <br />
        <partial name="../Common/ImageCard.cshtml" ,
            model='@new Image("/Blobs/Projects/LaserCut/DescentModels/green_robot.jpg", "The plans for the Class 1 drone being laser-cut.")' />
        <br />
        <partial name="../Common/ImageCard.cshtml" ,
            model='@new Image("/Blobs/Projects/LaserCut/DescentModels/green_rob.jpg", "The laser-cut Class 1 drone, assembled.")' />
        <br />
        <partial name="../Common/ImageCard.cshtml" ,
            model='@new Image("/Blobs/Projects/LaserCut/DescentModels/bluerobot_plans.png", "The laser-cut Class 2 drone, designed in Autodesk 123D Make.")' />
        <br />
        <partial name="../Common/ImageCard.cshtml" ,
            model='@new Image("/Blobs/Projects/LaserCut/DescentModels/blue_rob.jpg", "The laser-cut Class 2 drone, assembled.")' />
        <br />
        <partial name="../Common/ParagraphStart.cshtml" />
        If you'll want to download these models for yourself, be prepared for some complications! First, you'll need to use the
        <a href="http://archive.org/web/web.php">Internet Archive Wayback Machine</a> to acquire the files. After that, <a href="http://brlcad.org/%22">BRL-CAD</a>
        is one of the few programs that can properly convert the unusual 3D model structure into .STL files for import into Autodesk 123D Make.
        <partial name="../Common/ParagraphEnd.cshtml" />
        <br />
    </div>
</div>